
[1]surname

   SUR'NAME, n. [L. super and nomen.]

   1. An additional name; a name or appellation added to the baptismal or
   christian name,and which becomes a family name. Surnames, with us,
   originally designated occupation, estate, place of residence, or some
   particular thing or event that related to the person. Thus William
   Rufus or red; Edmund Ironsides; Robert Smith,or the smith; William
   Turner.

   2. An appellation added to the original name.

   My surname Coriolanus.
